  "text": "In this section, the first-principle model to predict TD temp is explained. This first-principle model consists of two parts; the first one models phenomena during the transportation period from the secondary refining to the continuous casting, and the second one models phenomena during the casting period. In this model, the degradation of ladles is taken into account. Molten Steel in Ladle It is assumed that the ladle is a cylinder of radius R i . On the basis of the CFD simulation results, indicating that thermal stratification is formed vertically in the standing ladle due to natural convection [CITATION_1] ), the molten steel temperature is modeled as a function of time t and position z from the bottom of the ladle.",
